When using Service Cloud Voice, it's helpful to understand the terms used to talk about telephony.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise and Unlimited Editions, Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, and Government Cloud as an add-on license. Government Cloud is supported only on Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect and Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony.

When you create a Service Cloud Voice contact center with Amazon Connect, Salesforce creates two connected apps for you: Single Sign-On Connected App and REST API OAuth Connected App.

A Contact Center represents the agents and supervisors providing customer service with Service Cloud Voice. An IVR (Interactive Voice Response) is a telephony menu system that helps callers navigate to the right department in your contact center.

If using Amazon Connect as your telephony provider, customize your IVR by working with its two key ingredients: Lambda functions and contact flows. A contact flow is a sequence of steps that determine how customers interact with your contact center. Salesforce provides sample contact flows for use in configuring inbound, outbound, and transferred call flows.

Lambda functions are small pieces of code used in Amazon Connect to configure your phone system's IVR. Salesforce provides several Lambda functions for use in Service Cloud Voice contact flows. These functions perform actions such as creating a voice call record in Salesforce, starting real-time transcription, saving transcripts to Salesforce, and syncing data between a contact trace record (CTR) and a VoiceCall record.

To learn more about the Lambda functions that Salesforce provides, see Lambda functions.

Phone number porting connects your existing phone number or numbers to work with your new contact center. To avoid anxiety about the porting timeline, claim a new phone number for testing and production and forward traffic to that number from your original production phone number until testing is complete. Then, port the original production phone number from your previous telephony provider to your new one.

A softphone is a software-based phone that agents access from a computer. The softphone interface resembles a regular phone but offers extra functions like transferring callers to another agent or queue, muting your line, and placing a caller on hold.

The Telephony Provider is the back-end telephony service integrated with Service Cloud Voice, by default using Amazon Connect as its provider.
title: Service Cloud Voice Key Concepts
